cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with automatic speech recognition systems and the impact of accents on their performance. It could also belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it deals with acoustic models. Additionally, it involves machine learning techniques, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, it could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with the impact of different accents on speech recognition.
